file=Engineering/axiom/custom/dsa-design-records/assets/dsa-record-template.md · ddr:DSA Design Record — DSR-[NNN] — [choice name]=> ADR for algorithms/data structures. Append-only; a reversal is a new DSR citing this one. Credit: pattern from dev/architecture-decisions.\n\n**Status:** proposed / accepted / superseded-by DSR-NNN \· **Date:** YYYY-MM-DD \· **Reviewed by:** [raj/dana/…]\n · tb=\| operation \| frequency \| latency sensitivity \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| [lookup / range / insert / ordered-iter / delete] \| [hot/warm/cold] \| \| · tb=\| option \| time (worst / amortized) \| space \| justifying invariant \| notes \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| A: [structure] \| \| \| [why the bound holds] \| \| · tb=\| B: [structure] \| \| \| \| \| · d:Decision=[chosen option] because [the operation mix + constraints that select it].\n · tk(:Trade-offs kept (the reasons someone will later want to change this)=- [cost of the chosen structure — e.g., no ordering / memory overhead / rebalance cost]\n · cs(:Complexity summary (the claim, checkable)=- [operation]: O(…) [worst], O(…) [amortized] — because [invariant]\n- Where constants / real-n dominate asymptotics: [note → performance-profiling ref]\n · s/s:Supersedes / superseded by=[DSR-refs]\n